args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the Stirring Shadows event.
Akasha! Just who I was lookin' for.
Oh? And what might I do for you, Luca?
Well, I went a little overboard on the\napple picking today, so I figured I'd\ncome share a few with ya.
Akasha, would you mind taste testing\nmy latest recipe?
But of course. Your cooking is ever\nso delicious, Cleo.
Akasha, about that matter we discussed\npreviously...
Ah, yes. My ears are yours.
...What's all this?\nHmm, I remember her... That's Akasha...
When exactly did you all come to know\nthat woman? Akasha, that is.
Whaddya mean? We've been buds with\nher what for ages.
Hello there, Heinwald.\nFancy seeing you here.
Quite. Though this is far from a chance\nencounter, I suspect. It seems something\nmore treacherous is afoot.
Heh heh. Merely a mark of my\nadmiration for you.
Besides, are my methods truly\nso treacherous?
I may well have met the people here\nin the past, or perhaps even the future.
It's simply coincidence that it's only come\nto light now.
And thus my presence here, in this way,\nat this time, is exceedingly natural.
Hm. An intriguing perspective.\nAnd terrific sophistry, besides.
We're on the same team now.\nLet us form a warm bond.
I came here only to see you, after all.
I'm honored, truly—and yet I have to\nwonder why.
Since the moment we met, you have\nremained ever in my thoughts.
I came to realize that the two of us could\nsurely understand each other.
And there we have our first point of\ndiscussion. Precisely what do you\nmean by ＂understand＂?
I worry we may not be quite as attuned\nas you would like.
You seek knowledge, and attain it. As luck\nwould have it, I am one and the same.
I suspect that is only the beginning of\nour commonalities.
You are right about one thing, at least:\nI do crave the truths of the world.
But I think you prefer riddles to\nknowledge itself.

Heh heh. Think on this then, mmm?
Say a person loves a labyrinth.
What do you suspect they enjoy
more: the entrance, or the exit?
You imply there's no difference,\nbut that is only more sophistry.
I have little need to be clung to by\nsomeone so inscrutable.
You aren't the only one who has attained\nsomething through knowledge.
That is me, from another time.\nAnd so begins the tale...
These theatrics are a bit much for a simple\nmemoir, no?
But so long as you're going that far,\nI do hope you make it entertaining.
